<p>Only ID value = 1 is common for all three tables so this will be the only record preserved after joining all of them:</p>

<div class="language-sql highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">SELECT</span> <span class="n">left_id</span><span class="p">,</span>
       <span class="n">left_val</span><span class="p">,</span>
       <span class="n">right_val</span><span class="p">,</span>
       <span class="n">another_val</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span>   <span class="n">left_table</span> <span class="n">l</span>
       <span class="k">INNER</span> <span class="k">JOIN</span> <span class="n">right_table</span> <span class="n">r</span>
               <span class="k">ON</span> <span class="n">l</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">left_id</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">right_id</span>
       <span class="k">INNER</span> <span class="k">JOIN</span> <span class="n">another_table</span> <span class="n">a</span>
               <span class="k">ON</span> <span class="n">l</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">left_id</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">a</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">another_id</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Output:</p>
