<h1 id="full-outer-join">FULL OUTER JOIN</h1>

<p><strong>FULL OUTER JOIN</strong> is a combination of left join and right join. It returns all records from both tables whether they have matches in the other table or not.</p>

<div class="language-sql highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">SELECT</span> <span class="o">*</span>
<span class="k">FROM</span>   <span class="n">left_table</span> <span class="n">l</span>
       <span class="k">FULL</span> <span class="k">OUTER</span> <span class="k">JOIN</span> <span class="n">right_table</span> <span class="n">r</span>
                    <span class="k">ON</span> <span class="n">l</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">left_id</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">right_id</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Output:</p>
<style type="text/css">
.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}
